    {
      "term": "distinct_messages_need_distinct_marks",
      "gloss": "the converse side of coding, at its smallest: a lossless code gives distinct messages distinct marks, and a mark-space smaller than the message-space cannot supply them — two bits of message will not ride one bit of mark; on a two-valued wire some pair of the four collides. the constant cited was carved as the floor of contact width; read from this seat it is the zeroth coding bound, the counting argument the coding converses run at scale. this entry is the floor without the price — what the price is, on average, is the terminus's question.",
